While most of us weared jeans, T-shirts, he often showed up in bold outfits. Sometimes in bright colours, sometimes with artistic or cultural patterns, or sometimes that looks vintage or futuristic. For example, I remember once he came to class wearing long purple coat, bright orange pants, and a leopard-painted shirt that he said he had designed himself. Everyone turned to look at him not in a negative way, but out of pure curiosity. The funny thing is that he pulled it off with so much confidence that it somehow worked. He also loved wearing accessories like funky sunglasses, large rings, or even hats that look like something out of a fashion magazine or a movie set.
